config BR2_PACKAGE_LIBCHDR
	bool "libchdr"
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ZLIB
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ZSTD
	# BR2_PACKAGE_LZMA_SDK is not an upstream Buildroot symbol -- it is
	# this tree's own BR2_EXTERNAL sibling (package/lzma-sdk), sourced
	# into the same Kconfig tree, so the select is legal.
	select BR2_PACKAGE_LZMA_SDK
	help
	  libchdr: MAME's CHD (Compressed Hunks of Data) read library,
	  maintained standalone by rtissera. Used by Main_MiSTer's cores
	  support for CD-image formats -- PSX/MegaCD/Saturn/etc. cores
	  mount .chd disc images through the chd_* API.

	  Built as a shared library (libchdr.so.0.3) against the SYSTEM
	  zlib, libzstd and liblzma-sdk instead of upstream's vendored
	  deps/ copies -- zlib/zstd via upstream's own WITH_SYSTEM_*
	  options, the LZMA SDK via this package's patches (0001-0003),
	  which add the missing WITH_SYSTEM_LZMA leg in upstream's own
	  pattern. Only the header-only dr_flac decoder stays bundled
	  (public domain / MIT-0; no shared-lib alternative exists, see
	  libchdr.mk).

	  The library exports ONLY chd_* symbols (upstream links with a
	  version script, src/link.T), so it cannot collide with
	  minizip-ng's mz_* namespace or anything else in Main's link.

	  https://github.com/rtissera/libchdr
